ANC Councillor Cybert Kabelo Ramodisha (36) has appeared before Giyani Magistrate court for selling and issuing fraudulent permits of movement of people to other provinces. He was arrested on Friday 1 May at Makgakgapaji village following a tip off f from community members. He sold between R250 and R800. NPA spokesperson Mashudu Malabi-Dzhangi said the informer got the permit with an amount of R100 after he made an agreement that he will pay the remaining amount of R150. Upon arrival at the said place they found three other clients waiting to buy the permits where one of them told the police that she arranged with the councilor to come and get the permit for authorizing her to travel to Gauteng for school. She said the accused was arrested immediately after he failed to explain to the police about the fake permits which he was selling. Laptop, cellphones and printer which he was using to type and print the permits was confiscated during the arrest. The accused is out on bail of R2000. The matter was postponed to 14 July 2020 